name: proposed-wilderness-areas-of-grand-canyon-national-park-arizona-generated-in-2003-by-the-interm
notes: This shapefile contains boundaries for Proposed Recommended Wilderness, Proposed Potential Wilderness, and Non-Wilderness in Grand Canyon National Park, Arizona. This dataset is derived from the latest official NPS Wilderness Study based on careful study of roadless areas, public hearings, and written responses. This study was never forwarded to Congress, and no formal designation of Wilderness has occured. This dataset has been revised from the Wilderness Study map to adjust buffers along roads and utilities, account for changes to the boundary and land status, and reflect more accurate measurement available through new GIS technology. This dataset identifies 951,254.63 acres within Grand Canyon National Park as Proposed Recommended Wilderness (980,088 acres in 1980), 135,667.86 acres as Proposed Potential Wilderness (131,814 acres in 1980). The remaining 123,340.97 acres of the park were determined to be not suitable for wilderness designation or potential wilderness at this time.
